# Lifecycle — {{ project_name }}

Phase and gate state for this project: **Discovery → Delivery → Deployment**.
This file is the machine-readable status contract — DSSG's project-mgmt-ai
(and any other tooling) reads it from the repo to draft project updates.

Written by `/gate-check` only. Do not hand-edit the block below — it is an
audit result, not an aspiration. The one exception is `rfc_approved`, which
mirrors a human-set `Status: APPROVED` line in RFC.md; `/gate-check` only
copies it.

```yaml
schema: 1
project: {{ project_slug }}
phase: discovery # discovery | delivery | deployment
updated: null # ISO date of last /gate-check run
milestone: null # current milestone from TASKS.md, e.g. "M1"
blocking_open_questions: null # count from DESIGN.md Open Questions (deferred excluded)
gates:
  G1_discovery_exit:
    design_no_blocking_open_questions: false # DESIGN.md: every open question resolved or Deferred(<trigger>)
    eval_targets_defined: false # DESIGN.md Evaluation table seeded into evals/targets.yaml
    base_scaffold_ci_green: false # project rendered; CI/test workflow passing
    milestones_and_m1_tasks_reviewed: false # /define-milestones + /sprint-kickoff artifacts exist, /plan-review done
    rfc_approved: false # RFC.md Status: APPROVED (human-set; mirrored here)
  G2_delivery_exit:
    eval_gate_green: false # `make eval-gate` passes against targets.yaml
    security_review_clean: false # /security-review findings resolved
    sanyi_audit_clean: false # /sanyi audit passes the change contract
    deployment_target_resolved: false # DESIGN.md deployment decision no longer Open/Deferred
    runbook_monitoring_documented: false # operator model + monitoring plan written
```

